Clone a depository
    --> Create a depository on Github
    --> On Github click code and copy the url of the depository 
    --> On terminal --> git clone "the url of the depository"

Push
    --> Add --> we add the files in the selected directory
            --> git add + name of the files
            --> if we have more files --> git add file1 /file2 /file3 /

    --> Commit --> git commit -m "Message to add to the commit"

    --> Push --> to push into our remote repository all the files/changes done in local 
             --> git push

Pull
    --> git pull --> we use this command to update our local branch with the remote branch

Branch
    --> git branch --> to create a new branch --> git branch new_branch
    --> git checkout --> to change branche --> git chekout new branch
    --> git checkout -b <new-branch> --> we can create and check a new branch at the same time